# Dynamic detail pages (site/category/tag/blog) — all routed through the single
# router in 404.html, which already contains the full renderSiteDetailPage /
# renderCategoryPage / renderTagPage / renderBlogPage implementation.
# IMPORTANT: rewrite target is "/404" (NOT "/404.html") — Cloudflare Pages
# unconditionally 301-redirects any resolved *.html file access to its
# extension-less form, so a literal "/404.html" target causes every single
# match to bounce to /404 in the address bar. "/404" is already the canonical
# form, so no further redirect happens.
# Bare index paths (/category/, /tag/, /blog/, /site/) are NOT rewritten here —
# those are real files served natively by Cloudflare. Rewriting them to their
# own index.html causes the same class of redirect loop (Cloudflare bounces
# .../index.html back to its own canonical directory URL), so leave them alone.
/category         /category/       301
/category/:slug   /404              200
/category/:slug/  /404              200

/tag              /tag/            301
/tag/:slug        /404              200
/tag/:slug/       /404              200

/search           /search/         301

/blog             /blog/           301
/blog/:slug       /404              200
/blog/:slug/      /404              200

